to\u2010one mapping of axes and clusters. Stepping down seems promising as a means of illustrating clusters of samples, especially when there are subtle or complex discontinuities in gradients.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Alroy, John", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/eaea60a2d40734d0f739a6e7f0014c86", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/3703bd26634e17b0a7d4a230801c985dc7607f6412359e2239961a95edbb5786", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/FAS4UQ6M", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/FAS4UQ6M", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/715848fefcfa1e108bced550c6fd26c2!/b269575-272015", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "9", "pages": "1504-1513", "title": "Ecography", "volume": "42"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/eaea60a2d40734d0f739a6e7f0014c86"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:FAS4UQ6M"}, {"identifier": "10.1111/ecog.04464"}], "communities": [{"id": "batlit"}, {"id": "biosyslit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid", "pid_value": "13467787"}}]}}, "title": "Discovering biogeographic and ecological clusters with a graph theore